reviews.text: The cafe is now a generic poor substitute to the previous cafe and owners. The service is bland, no character, no conversation, someone is on their mobile all the time, no customer service. The food choice is boring and does not entice. Bring back the previous cafe!!! A million per cent better than this.

I went in to the station, dropped off my wife, and asked about a Senior Rail card being an Old Aged pensioner. There was a queue when I picked up the form and the leaflet and there was a problem processing the form after  i had queued up again having filled it in. I bought this Senior Rail Card for 30 pounds to try to save some money being a pensioner. However a month later, I got a Parking Notice from APCOA Parking because I had strayed a few minutes over the 20 minutes free parking and received a fine of 85 pounds.
I appealed following the process outlined in the Fine Notice, explaining and sending them a copy of my senior rail card. They have now just rejected my appeal and said if i don’t pay quickly they will take court action against me.
My senior rail card therefore cost me 115 pounds.
My advice is don’t go anywhere near Warwick Parkway station or any APCOA Parking with your car.

Good, clean station. Plenty of trains to Birmingham and London and lots of parking. If you’re going to Warwick use Warwick station as it’s quite a walk or a bus ride into Warwick from here. Close to A46 and M40.
